messages.message:
<!subteam^S07855GV3GV> seeing a weird issue where 2/3 of the parallel cypress runs in cypress CI are failing https://github.com/instabase/instabase/actions/runs/14335989266/job/40190376748 (see `Run cypress tests against sandbox - blocking tests` step) its affecting some other PRs as well

It looks like the environments that the tests are running on out of sync (they have different chrome version somehow) Iâ€™m going to try recreating the sandbox and see if that fixes it
Seems like `Cypress (3)` is using `"browserVersion": "135.0.7049.52.... (Expected: 135)",` instead of `"browserVersion": "134.0.6998.165.... (Expected: 135)",`

https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/69616
Relevant github issue: cypress-io/github-action#911 (comment) (https://github.com/cypress-io/github-action/issues/911#issuecomment-1544287426)

> During staged rollout of a new GitHub-hosted runner version, GitHub may provide a mixture of current and new image versions used by the container matrix. It is recommended to use a Docker image in the parallel job run which avoids any Cypress Cloud errors due to browser major version mismatch from the two different image versions. A Docker image is not necessary if testing against the default built-in Electron browser because this browser version is fixed by the Cypress version in use and it is unaffected by any GitHub runner image rollout
